# Enforce LF line endings for shell scripts and text files that run on Linux
# (CI runners, act). Without this, Windows checkouts can introduce CRLF and
# break bash interpretation (e.g., `set -o pipefail\r` becomes invalid).
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.bash      text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf
*.mk        text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
